That’s a strong set of completions — Bolt basically implemented the exact “enterprise-looking” controls we wanted (tiering, encryption, scoped cache, RLS, audit). The only things left are (a) sanity checks and (b) hardening the frontend delivery (security headers + caching rules).

2 quick sanity checks before we move on

DSBN shared history: Bolt’s summary says “All lookups scoped to user.” If you truly want shared history for DSBN, make sure DSBN users can read rows scoped to the org context (e.g., org_domain='dsbn.org'), not only their own user_id. (Easy policy tweak if needed.)

Free sources list: confirm the “ipapi” source is using HTTPS and doesn’t accidentally require a paid key (some “ip api” providers do). You previously had an ip-api.com style call; just ensure it’s HTTPS now.

If both are good, you’re already in the “web team won’t roast this” zone.

Yes — add a Cloudflare Pages _headers file

Cloudflare Pages supports a plain text _headers file placed in the static assets output directory; for Vite projects, putting it in public/_headers is the common move because it’s copied into the build output. 
Cloudflare Docs
+1

Recommended public/_headers (safe + practical for a React/Vite SPA)
/* 
  # Baseline hardening
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=(), usb=()
  X-Frame-Options: DENY

  # HSTS (enable once you're sure everything is HTTPS only)
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains

  # CSP (starter version; tighten after you test auth/login)
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; base-uri 'self'; object-src 'none'; frame-ancestors 'none'; img-src 'self' data: https:; font-src 'self' data: https:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; script-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://<YOUR_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF>.supabase.co wss://<YOUR_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF>.supabase.co;

Cache rules for “deploys update cleanly”
/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-store

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable


Why these help:

index.html changes each deploy → you want clients to fetch fresh.

Vite assets are fingerprinted → safe to cache “forever”.

What you need to change in that CSP line

Replace:

<YOUR_SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF> with your real Supabase project ref (the subdomain part)

If you also call anything else directly from the browser (ideally you don’t), add those to connect-src. Keeping all threat intel calls backend-only is cleaner and safer.

